    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div type="letter">
                <div type="text">
                    <opener>
                        <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                        <date>Jan 8<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1880</date>
                        <salute>My dear Lady Hooker</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <div type="transcription">
                        <p>I thank you much for your good wishes for all of us, &amp; for your very kind &amp; welcome present of the Bananas.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
                        <p>Pray believe me | Yours sincerely &amp; obliged | Charles Darwin</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                
            </div>
            
            
            
            
            
            <div type="footnotes">
                <note xml:id="foot.f1">Hooker’s letter has not been found. The Darwins occasionally received presents of bananas from the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew; see, for example, <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 25, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11238.xml">letter to Hyacinth Hooker, [18 November 1877]</ref>.</note>
                </div>
        
